                    Etymology
                </div>
                <div class="info-box-text">
                    <i>Sinomicrurus</i> is a compound word assembled from <i>Sino</i>, New Latin for "Chinese", 
                    and the Greek words <i>mikros</i> = small, and <i>ura</i> = tail; alluding to the short, pointy tails of this genus;
                    <br>        
                    <i>sauteri</i>: in honor of <a class="site-link" href="http://taiwanheute.nat.gov.tw/ct.asp?xItem=41966&CtNode=1580">Hans Sauter</a>, a Taiwan-based German entomologist who collected the type specimen for A. sauteri.
                    <br>
                    The Chinese name <span lang="zh-TW" id="text-chinese">梭德氏帶紋赤蛇</span> (suo1de2shi4dai4wen2chi4she2) means "Sauter's (<span lang="zh-TW" id="text-chinese">梭德氏</span>) Striped (<span lang="zh-TW" id="text-chinese">帶紋</span>) Red Snake (<span lang="zh-TW" id="text-chinese">赤蛇</span>)".
                </div>
